                <note rend="inline" type="source">314.115C43/125: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Geissler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-06-20T11:00:00-06:00"
                            >June 20, 1929—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>78. Accompanied by Davidson I communicated today to Minister for Foreign Affairs
                    Aguirre the contents of the Department’s telegram <pb facs="0256" n="138"
                        xml:id="pg_138"/> number 30, June 14, 6 p.m. He said that he knows nothing
                    about the matter, that however he will study it today, consult the President and
                    Cabinet tomorrow, and inform me immediately of the instructions he will
                    receive.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Geissler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
